    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Photographic prints made using a light-sensitive emulsion of a ferric salt and silver nitrate. When developed, a metallic silver image is formed; various developers can produce black, brown, purple, or maroon tones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
